      • getAccumuloOperationsInstance

        protected BasicAccumuloOperations getAccumuloOperationsInstance(String zookeepers,
                                                    String accumuloInstance,
                                                    String accumuloUser,
                                                    String accumuloPass,
                                                    String geowaveNamespace)
                                                         throws org.apache.accumulo.core.client.AccumuloException,
                                                                org.apache.accumulo.core.client.AccumuloSecurityException
        The class tells geowave about the accumulo instance it should connect to, as well as what tables it should create/store it's data in
        Parameters:
        zookeepers - Zookeepers associated with the accumulo instance, comma separate
        accumuloInstance - Accumulo instance name
        accumuloUser - User geowave should connect to accumulo as
        accumuloPass - Password for user to connect to accumulo
        geowaveNamespace - Different than an accumulo namespace (unfortunate naming usage) - this is basically a prefix on the table names geowave uses.
        Returns:
        Object encapsulating the accumulo connection information
        Throws:
        org.apache.accumulo.core.client.AccumuloException
        org.apache.accumulo.core.client.AccumuloSecurityException

      • createDataAdapter

        public static FeatureDataAdapter createDataAdapter(org.opengis.feature.simple.SimpleFeatureType sft)
        The dataadapter interface describes how to serialize a data type. Here we are using an implementation that understands how to serialize OGC SimpleFeature types.
        Parameters:
        sft - simple feature type you want to generate an adapter from
        Returns:
        data adapter that handles serialization of the sft simple feature type

      • createSpatialIndex

        public static Index createSpatialIndex()
        We need an index model that tells us how to index the data - the index determines -What fields are indexed -The precision of the index -The range of the index (min/max values) -The range type (bounded/unbounded) -The number of "levels" (different precisions, needed when the values indexed has ranges on any dimension)
        Returns:
        GeoWave index for a default SPATIAL index

      • createPointFeatureType

        public static org.opengis.feature.simple.SimpleFeatureType createPointFeatureType()
        A simple feature is just a mechanism for defining attributes (a feature is just a collection of attributes + some metadata) We need to describe what our data looks like so the serializer (FeatureDataAdapter for this case) can know how to store it. Features/Attributes are also a general convention of GIS systems in general.
        Returns:
        Simple Feature definition for our demo point feature
